<!-- 4.1.3 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 4.1.3</span>
	A map $\theta:S\to T$ between inverse semigroups is a partial morphism if and only if for all $s,t\in S$,
	<ol class='roman'>
		<li>
			$\theta(s^*)=\theta(s)^*$;
		</li>
		
		<li>
			$\theta(s)\theta(t) \leq\theta(st)$;
		</li>
		
		<li>
			$\theta(s)\leq\theta(t)$ whenever $s\leq t$.
		</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
</div>